Use the Salesforce and Flowdock APIs

Setup:
=====
• Python3 virtual environment (e.g. virtualenv -p python3 env)
pip install -r req.txt

• config/ → Your configuration, including OAuth2 tokens
cp sforce-config.json.template sforce-config.json

This page explains how to find the fields (cliend_id, client_secret, etc.):
http://www.salesforce.com/us/developer/docs/api_rest/Content/intro_understanding_web_server_oauth_flow.htm

Run ./show-sforce-api-versions.py to see the options for the ‘apiVersionUrl’.

• current directory
Always have your current directory set to the one containing this README file.

Test:
====
./test.sh
